      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(providers): release stream reader lock after classifying SDK stream body",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`src/agents/provider-transport-fetch.ts:351` calls `reader.cancel()` in the finally block of `classifyOpenAISdkStreamBody` but never calls `reader.releaseLock()`. The established codebase pattern calls both (see `http-error-body.ts:11`, `provider-http-errors.ts:44`, `voice-call/response-body.ts:28`).\n\nThis is **D3**: defensive lock release matching codebase conventions.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/agents/provider-transport-fetch.ts`: add `reader.releaseLock()` in finally block alongside `reader.cancel()`\n\n**Scope**: 3 lines. Purely defensive.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Existing tests continue to pass\n\nThe change is a defensive lock release matching the established pattern used in `http-error-body.ts`, `provider-http-errors.ts`, and `voice-call/response-body.ts`. No behavioral change — `cancel()` already releases the lock implicitly.",
